actions.committee: House Committee on Post Office and Civil Service
actions.text: Referred to the House Committee on Post Office and Civil Service.
Committee on Post Office and Civil Service discharged.
Mr. Wynn asked unanimous consent to discharge from committee and consider.
Motion to reconsider laid on the table Agreed to without objection.
Received in the Senate and read twice and referred to the Committee on Judiciary.
Senate Committee on Judiciary discharged by Unanimous Consent.
Passed Senate without amendment and with a preamble by Voice Vote.
Message on Senate action sent to the House.

summary.text: Authorizes the President to designate the last Friday of April 1993 as National Arbor Day.
